      • getSubViewer

        public StateflowChart getSubViewer()
        Returns a chart (subview) if this chart state is actually a subchart. If this state does not wrap a subchart (isSubChart()==false) this method returns null. In stateflow, a subchart is a chart that is shown in another (parent) chart. We model subcharts as stateflow states because they are rendered similar to states and the subchart's contents are not rendered. You can render the subchart by passing it to StateflowChartRenderer.renderChart().
